replyContent: Hi Chris, I believe you're referring to a video that wasn't created by us and simply referred to in the app as another reference for learning the Wing Per Ring theory. I'm sure if you do a search on YouTube you'll find plenty of videos that try to explain it. Thanks!

content: Like it. Need to check calculation on Nirvana @ 100% accuracy thou. 8 mph wind and it says 5.3 or there about. Even the outside ring says 3.5. That's over 10 rings right there. You say 0.7 PR so 8.0/ 0.7=11.7. What's up with that? Thanks

replyContent: Thanks for the review! We'll look into the transparency on the wind entry, it might be that the colours can be made less saturated. It's a careful balancing act obviously with readability :)
